{
  "doc_id": "8335",
  "text": "ELISpot assays have become the standard method to quantify IFNγ production in many laboratories because they are easy to perform, do not require investment in expensive equipment (e.g. flow cytometers) and are sensitive for the detection of even low numbers of antigenspecific cells [CITATION_1] . However, ELISpot assays have several important limitations: relatively large volumes of blood are required to obtain sufficient PBMCs for analysis; the process of extracting and purifying PBMCs may cause their activation and alter their phenotype [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] ; assays cannot be re-run unless stored samples of cells are available.",
